{"id": "test-00414", "text": "NFL AMERICAN FOOTBALL-COLTS CLOBBER EAGLES TO STAY IN PLAYOFF HUNT.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 3, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "NFL"}, {"start": 36, "end": 42, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "EAGLES"}]}
{"id": "test-00415", "text": "INDIANAPOLIS 1996-12-06", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 12, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "INDIANAPOLIS"}]}
{"id": "test-00416", "text": "The injury-plagued Indianapolis Colts lost another quarterback on Thursday but last year's AFC finalists rallied together to shoot down the Philadelphia Eagles 37-10 in a showdown of playoff contenders.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 19, "end": 37, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Indianapolis Colts"}, {"start": 140, "end": 159, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Philadelphia Eagles"}]}
{"id": "test-00417", "text": "Marshall Faulk rushed for 101 yards and two touchdowns and Jason Belser returned an interception 44 yards for a score as the Colts improved to 8-6, the same mark as the Eagles, who lost for the fourth time in five games.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 14, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Marshall Faulk"}, {"start": 59, "end": 71, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Jason Belser"}, {"start": 125, "end": 130, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Colts"}, {"start": 169, "end": 175, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Eagles"}]}
{"id": "test-00418", "text": "Paul Justin, starting for the sidelined Jim Harbaugh, was 14-of-23 for 144 yards and a touchdown for the the Colts, who played their last home game of the season.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 11, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Paul Justin"}, {"start": 40, "end": 52, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Jim Harbaugh"}, {"start": 109, "end": 114, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Colts"}]}
{"id": "test-00419", "text": "Indianapolis closes with games at Kansas City and Cincinnati.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 12, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Indianapolis"}, {"start": 34, "end": 45, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Kansas City"}, {"start": 50, "end": 60, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Cincinnati"}]}
{"id": "test-00420", "text": "The Eagles were held without a touchdown until the final five seconds.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 4, "end": 10, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Eagles"}]}
{"id": "test-00421", "text": "Philadelphia, which fell from an NFC East tie with the Dallas Cowboys and Washington Redskins, go on the road against the New York Jets and then entertain Arizona.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 12, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Philadelphia"}, {"start": 55, "end": 69, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Dallas Cowboys"}, {"start": 74, "end": 93, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Washington Redskins"}, {"start": 122, "end": 135, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "New York Jets"}, {"start": 155, "end": 162, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Arizona"}]}
{"id": "test-00422", "text": "The loss by Philadelphia allowed the idle Green Bay Packers (10-3) to clinch the first NFC playoff berth.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 12, "end": 24, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Philadelphia"}, {"start": 42, "end": 59, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Green Bay Packers"}]}
{"id": "test-00423", "text": "The Colts won despite the absence of injured starting defensive tackle Tony Siragusa, cornerback Ray Buchanan and linebacker Quentin Coryatt.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 4, "end": 9, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Colts"}, {"start": 71, "end": 84, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Tony Siragusa"}, {"start": 97, "end": 109, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Ray Buchanan"}, {"start": 125, "end": 140, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Quentin Coryatt"}]}
{"id": "test-00424", "text": "Faulk carried 16 times, including a 13-yard TD run in the first quarter and a seven-yard score early in the final period.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 5, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Faulk"}]}
{"id": "test-00425", "text": "Justin made his second straight start for Harbaugh, who has a knee injury.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Justin"}, {"start": 42, "end": 50, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Harbaugh"}]}
{"id": "test-00426", "text": "Justin suffered a sprained right shoulder in the third quarter and did not return.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Justin"}]}
{"id": "test-00427", "text": "Third-stringer Kerwin Bell, a 1988 draft choice of the Miami Dolphins, made his NFL debut and was 5-of-5 for 75 yards, including a 20-yard scoring strike to Marvin Harrison in the third period.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 15, "end": 26, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Kerwin Bell"}, {"start": 55, "end": 69, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Miami Dolphins"}, {"start": 80, "end": 83, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "NFL"}, {"start": 157, "end": 172, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Marvin Harrison"}]}
{"id": "test-00428", "text": "A 39-yard interference penalty against Philadelphia's Troy Vincent set up Faulk's first score around left end that capped an 80-yard march 5:17 into the game and the rout was on.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 39, "end": 51, "ent_type": "LOC", "text": "Philadelphia"}, {"start": 54, "end": 66, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Troy Vincent"}, {"start": 74, "end": 79, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Faulk"}]}
{"id": "test-00429", "text": "Eagles quarterback Ty Detmer was 17-of-34 for 182 yards before he was benched.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 6, "ent_type": "ORG", "text": "Eagles"}, {"start": 19, "end": 28, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Ty Detmer"}]}
{"id": "test-00430", "text": "Ricky Watters, who leads the NFC in rushing, left the game after getting kneed to the helmet after gaining 33 yards on seven carries.", "gold_mentions": [{"start": 0, "end": 13, "ent_type": "PER", "text": "Ricky Watters"}]}
